This role is for a full-time position.

** Why you’ll love working here. **

Are you able to demonstrate your expertise in web technologies on the .NET
stack? If the answer is yes and you’re ready to evolve these skills in a
supportive team, we'd love to meet you. You’ll be offered…

  * A competitive salary package. 
  * Working from your home or your preferred location. 
  * Training and Development allowance. 
  * Coaching, mentoring and support for training, growth and advancement. 
  * Opportunity to shape and grow the role. 
  * A wide range of technologies and challenges. 
  * Access to our employee perks program. 

If you have no experience in one or two areas but know you can learn quickly
or have experience of similar, just let us know. We value people who can
follow the job specs but also discern what’s needed to get the job done.

Our approach to diversity is simple: Be Yourself. We like it that way. From
cultivating a culture where all employees can bring their best selves to work
to deploying diversity initiatives that support all, we’re doing what it takes
to build a more equitable workplace.

** About Your IT Team. **

Your IT Team is a fast-growing Australian IT and technology consultancy. We
have a passion for making a difference through the responsible and innovative
application of advanced software, experimentation, and technology. Looking for
more effective and simpler ways of solving technical problems is at the heart
of our team culture. We are always interested in what's new and how applying
emergent technologies may benefit our close clients and their business
objectives.

At Your IT Team, the team enjoy working on challenging problems with leaders
in their field and leveraging multi-disciplinary backgrounds to develop
creative, novel and state-of-the-art solutions, all while having fun.

Your IT Team is proud to be an inclusive and equal opportunity organisation.
We embrace it, value it, celebrate it and support it for the benefit of our
employees, our customers and our community. Our team is provided with an
environment to excel, with professional development opportunities and the
flexibility and support to develop new ideas, services or products. Team
members are encouraged and supported to shape the future of Your IT Team.

We wouldn’t be who we are without the team that we have, so we provide
generous employment conditions, family-friendly policies and flexible work
arrangements to enable our staff to maintain a good work-life balance, along
with some unique opportunities for the innovators amongst us. There is no
fixed office, we operate fully remotely, but our awesome team, based around
Australia, Asia and Europe, have big hearts and are from diverse backgrounds.
So, while we don’t all work in the same room, we work with the same purpose,
regularly connecting via video chats.

We are currently expanding and looking for a motivated and qualified Senior
.NET Web Developer with a drive to learn and challenge themselves - could that
be you?

** Key Skills and Desired Experience. **

  * You must have at least 5 years of commercial experience. 
  * ASP.Net/.Net Core MVC and/or Razor Pages including Web API. 
  * Recent MVC-Based CMS Experience. 
  * HTML5, JavaScript and CSS, SASS, Webpack, Grunt. 
  * Solid backend software development skills & experience. 
  * Solid frontend software development skills & experience. 
  * SQL Server / Transact-SQL. 
  * Know your way around Visual Studio and vsCode. 
  * Know how to work with GIT. 
  * Understanding of agile development processes. 
  * Excellent customer service and communication skills. 
  * Fired up by the potential of technology. 
  * Loves finding simple solutions to complex problems. 

** Highly Regarded. **

  * MCP/MCSD Certification in relevant technologies. 
  * Experience with React JS, VueJS or other relevant frameworks. 
  * Experience with Umbraco. 
  * Experience with Azure Cloud services. 
  * Unit Testing. 
  * Experience with Azure Search. 

** What you’ll do. **

The Senior Developer will have mastered the technology they are expected to
work with and be able to instruct others. Your IT Group values the
contribution of its staff in all areas and so the opportunity to shape the
structure, practices and processes of the business will be present.

Project-Related:

  * Solution Development and Delivery 
    * Creates efficient and logical databases for clients. 
    * Designs and codes superior technical solutions. 
    * Easily recognises system deficiencies and implements effective solutions. 
  * Project Execution 
    * Creates and executes project work plans and revises as appropriate to meet changing needs and requirements. 
    * Communicates and enforces coding standards. 
    * Lead the technical design and implementation of software products across a team of developers. 
    * Own issues, drive and coordinate to meet delivery timescales/milestones. 
    * Review code developed by other developers and provide feedback to ensure best practices (e.g., style guidelines, checking code in, accuracy, testability, and efficiency). 
    * Write secure, well-tested, performant, and quality code. 
    * Consistently delivers high-quality services to clients. 

Career-path competencies

  * Communication 
    * Assists in the facilitation of team and client meetings. 
    * Delivers informative, well-organized presentations. 
    * Understands how to communicate difficult/sensitive information tactfully. 
    * Share knowledge through technical documentation, technical write-ups, and technical presentations. 
  * Relational Databases 
    * Understands complex database concepts as well as the implications of different database designs. 
    * Effectively employs many different database design techniques. 
    * Possesses demonstrated work experience with more than one relational database management system. 
  * Programming Languages 
    * Demonstrates expert knowledge of at least one structured programming language. 
    * Understands the benefits of various programming languages. 
    * Develop specialist knowledge in relevant programming languages, tools, and techniques and apply expertise and knowledge to deliver effective solutions. 
  * Architecture 
    * Possesses significant knowledge of client-server, cloud, and internet systems architectures. 
    * Creates well-designed, reusable objects. 
    * Understands browser-specific compatibility issues. 
    * Understands the benefits of the various design methodologies and object-oriented environments. 
    * Understands the nuances of the Umbraco framework and best practices. 

Professional qualities

  * Leadership 
    * Generates enthusiasm among team members. 
    * Proactively seeks opportunities to serve in leadership roles. 
    * Challenges others to develop as leaders while serving as a role model. 
    * Manages the process of innovative change. 
    * Assists in the training and development of Junior staff. 
  * Teamwork 
    * Facilitates effective team interaction. 
    * Acknowledges and appreciates each team member's contributions. 
    * Supports the Project Manager in managing resources within budget and project schedule. 
  * Client Management 
    * Actively collaborate with product owners, stakeholders, technical specialists and other Your IT Team specialists to achieve effective and speedy development. 
    * Develops relationships with client personnel that foster ties with our clients. 
    * Communicates effectively with clients to identify needs and evaluate alternative business solutions with project management. 
    * Continually seeks opportunities to increase customer satisfaction and deepen client relationships. 
    * Manages client expectations effectively. 

Organisational responsibilities

  * Professional Development 
    * Conducts effective progress evaluations on time. 
    * Mentors those with less experience through informal channels. 
    * Seeks and participates in development opportunities above and beyond required training. 
    * Trains other employees through both formal and informal training programs. 
  * Internal Operations 
    * Identify opportunities for improvement in software development, engineering, security and testing approaches, processes and tools. 
    * Leads internal teams/task forces. 
    * Actively contributes to the corporate knowledge base. 
  * Responsibilities 
    * Contribution to the design of solutions in consultation with the Technology Architect. 
    * Deliver allocated technical deliverables per the development work plan within the estimates provided. 
    * Ensuring that the implemented solution is in line with the documentation and to raise issues of discrepancy immediately with the Project Management for review and rectification. 
    * Responsible for ensuring you adhere to the production and administrative guidelines of Your IT Group – including hours tracking, disciplined project communication and transparency in the development process. 
    * Provide estimates on new project work (including change requests for existing clients) in collaboration with the Team Lead consistent with the committed response times. 

** Training & Development **

The Senior Developer is expected to demonstrate a willingness to learn and
expand their knowledge. This may take the form of pursuing relevant
certification (Your IT Group may at its discretion pay or subsidise the cost
of training); researching new technology and ideas both at work and in
personal time; and presenting to peers on related topics.

The opportunity for attendance at industry-related conferences and forums
including but not limited to overseas Umbraco conferences will be given
occasionally.

